attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

effect.name: Table Service
effect.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Punch and Run
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sleep Spore
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 50 damage to itself.

data.name: Charizard-GX

attacks.name: Raging Destruction
attacks.text: Discard the top 8 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Fire Energy cards, attach them to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dreadful Flames-GX
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from each of your opponent's Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

rules: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

effect.name: Security Guard
effect.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, all of your Pokémon take 30 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Panic
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Hold Still
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

effect.name: Evasion Jutsu
effect.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Furious Shurikens
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Greninja-GX

effect.name: Elusive Master
effect.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is the last card in your hand, you may play it onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Mist Slash
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dark Mist-GX
attacks.text: Put 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your opponent's hand. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

rules: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Brilliant Deduction
attacks.text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

effect.name: Pantomime
effect.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may switch 1 of your facedown Prize cards with the top card of your deck.

attacks.name: Juggling
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Psyjack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that atttack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Break Burn
attacks.text: Discard 2 Psychic Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Mewtwo-GX

attacks.name: Telekinesis
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

attacks.name: Reigning Pulse
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Psychic Nova-GX
attacks.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

rules: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Directing Traffic
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

attacks.name: Cross Chop
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

attacks.name: Healing Melody
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Paralyzing Gaze
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Play Rough
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Continuous Lick
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Copy Anything
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack. If this Pokémon doesn't have the necessary Energy to use that attack, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Pitch
attacks.text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Lt. Yoshida
rules: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).
Your opponent reveals their hand. Draw 2 cards.
